<div class=" highlight hl-bash"><pre><span></span><span class="nb">echo</span> <span class="s2">&quot;Using conditional statement to create a project directory and project&quot;</span>

<span class="c1"># Variable section</span>
<span class="nb">export</span> <span class="nv">project_dir</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="nv">$HOME</span>/vscode  <span class="c1"># change vscode to different name to test git clone</span>
<span class="nb">export</span> <span class="nv">project</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="nv">$project_dir</span>/APCSPnoor  <span class="c1"># change APCSP to name of project from git clone</span>
<span class="nb">export</span> <span class="nv">project_repo</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">&quot;https://github.com/Unlqsting/APCSPnoor.git&quot;</span>  <span class="c1"># change to project of choice</span>

<span class="nb">cd</span> ~    <span class="c1"># start in home directory</span>

<span class="c1"># Conditional block to make a project directory</span>
<span class="k">if</span> <span class="o">[</span> ! -d <span class="nv">$project_dir</span> <span class="o">]</span>
<span class="k">then</span> 
    <span class="nb">echo</span> <span class="s2">&quot;Directory </span><span class="nv">$project_dir</span><span class="s2"> does not exists... makinng directory </span><span class="nv">$project_dir</span><span class="s2">&quot;</span>
    mkdir -p <span class="nv">$project_dir</span>
<span class="k">fi</span>
<span class="nb">echo</span> <span class="s2">&quot;Directory </span><span class="nv">$project_dir</span><span class="s2"> exists.&quot;</span> 

<span class="c1"># Conditional block to git clone a project from project_repo</span>
<span class="k">if</span> <span class="o">[</span> ! -d <span class="nv">$project</span> <span class="o">]</span>
<span class="k">then</span>
    <span class="nb">echo</span> <span class="s2">&quot;Directory </span><span class="nv">$project</span><span class="s2"> does not exists... cloning </span><span class="nv">$project_repo</span><span class="s2">&quot;</span>
    <span class="nb">cd</span> <span class="nv">$project_dir</span>
    git clone <span class="nv">$project_repo</span>
    <span class="nb">cd</span> ~
<span class="k">fi</span>
<span class="nb">echo</span> <span class="s2">&quot;Directory </span><span class="nv">$project</span><span class="s2"> exists.&quot;</span>
</pre></div>

# My Blog


_powered by [fastpages](https://github.com/fastai/fastpages)_


## What To Do Next?

Great!  You have setup your repo.  Now its time to start writing content.  Some helpful links:

- [Writing Blogs With Jupyter](https://github.com/fastai/fastpages#writing-blog-posts-with-jupyter)

- [Writing Blogs With Markdown](https://github.com/fastai/fastpages#writing-blog-posts-with-markdown)

- [Writing Blog Posts With Word](https://github.com/fastai/fastpages#writing-blog-posts-with-microsoft-word)

- [(Optional) Preview Your Blog Locally](_fastpages_docs/DEVELOPMENT.md)

Note: you may want to remove example blog posts from the `_posts`,  `_notebooks` or `_word` folders (but leave them empty, don&#39;t delete these folders) if you don&#39;t want these blog posts to appear on your site.

Please use the [nbdev &amp; blogging channel](https://forums.fast.ai/c/fastai-users/nbdev/48) in the fastai forums for any questions or feature requests.

<span class="k">if</span> <span class="o">[</span> -f <span class="s2">&quot;</span><span class="nv">$file</span><span class="s2">&quot;</span> <span class="o">]</span><span class="p">;</span> <span class="k">then</span>
    rm <span class="nv">$file</span>
<span class="k">fi</span>

tee -a <span class="nv">$file</span> &gt;/dev/null <span class="s">&lt;&lt;EOF</span>
<span class="s"># Show Generated Markdown</span>
<span class="s">This introductory paragraph and this line and the title above are generated using tee with the standard input (&lt;&lt;) redirection operator.</span>
<span class="s">- This bulleted element is still part of the tee body.</span>
<span class="s">EOF</span>

<span class="nb">echo</span> <span class="s2">&quot;- This bulleted element and lines below are generated using echo with standard output (&gt;&gt;) redirection operator.&quot;</span> &gt;&gt; <span class="nv">$file</span>
<span class="nb">echo</span> <span class="s2">&quot;- The list definition, as is, is using space to seperate lines.  Thus the use of commas and hyphens in output.&quot;</span> &gt;&gt; <span class="nv">$file</span>
<span class="nv">actions</span><span class="o">=(</span><span class="s2">&quot;ls,list-directory&quot;</span> <span class="s2">&quot;cd,change-directory&quot;</span> <span class="s2">&quot;pwd,present-working-directory&quot;</span> <span class="s2">&quot;if-then-fi,test-condition&quot;</span> <span class="s2">&quot;env,bash-environment-variables&quot;</span> <span class="s2">&quot;cat,view-file-contents&quot;</span> <span class="s2">&quot;tee,write-to-output&quot;</span> <span class="s2">&quot;echo,display-content-of-string&quot;</span> <span class="s2">&quot;echo_text_&gt;\$file,write-content-to-file&quot;</span> <span class="s2">&quot;echo_text_&gt;&gt;\$file,append-content-to-file&quot;</span><span class="o">)</span>
<span class="k">for</span> action in <span class="si">${</span><span class="nv">actions</span><span class="p">[@]</span><span class="si">}</span><span class="p">;</span> <span class="k">do</span>  <span class="c1"># for loop is very similar to other language, though [@], semi-colon, do are new</span>
  <span class="nv">action</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="si">${</span><span class="nv">action</span><span class="p">//-/ </span><span class="si">}</span>  <span class="c1"># convert dash to space</span>
  <span class="nv">action</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="si">${</span><span class="nv">action</span><span class="p">//,/: </span><span class="si">}</span> <span class="c1"># convert comma to colon</span>
  <span class="nv">action</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="si">${</span><span class="nv">action</span><span class="p">//_text_/ </span><span class="se">\&quot;</span><span class="nv">sample</span><span class="p"> text</span><span class="se">\&quot;</span><span class="p"> </span><span class="si">}</span> <span class="c1"># convert _text_ to sample text, note escape character \ to avoid &quot;&quot; having meaning</span>
  <span class="nb">echo</span> <span class="s2">&quot;    - </span><span class="si">${</span><span class="nv">action</span><span class="p">//-/ </span><span class="si">}</span><span class="s2">&quot;</span> &gt;&gt; <span class="nv">$file</span>  <span class="c1"># echo is redirected to file with &gt;&gt;</span>
<span class="k">done</span>
